    // To minimize the sum, we want to replace larger numbers with the smallest possible divisors they can be replaced by.
    // The smallest possible value any element can be replaced by is the greatest common divisor (GCD) of itself and any other element it can be reduced to.
    // However, the process is more about propagation. If x % y == 0, x can become y.
    // This implies that any number reachable from the original set through division must be a divisor of some original number.
    // More accurately, if we can transform nums[a] to nums[b], and nums[b] can be transformed to nums[c], then nums[a] can effectively become nums[c].
    // This means all numbers that can be reduced to the same value (or a set of values) share a common divisor relationship.

